cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the assessment of bone age from X-ray images. The use of deep learning feature representation and multi-scale context information also suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The exploration of part selection and the joint training of modules may also indicate relevance to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the use of medical imaging data may suggest relevance to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
